{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3085949,"name":"Dresden Friar","username":"Dresden","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/e9c0ed/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-09-30T22:40:07.666Z","cooked":"<p>My team has been trying to get a bot with MK4I modules up and running using Team 364’s <a href="https://github.com/Team364/BaseFalconSwerve" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Swerve Code</a>. We’ve gotten to a point where two of the modules function perfectly fine, but the other two are being problematic.</p>
<p>The modules that aren’t working can strafe and turn perfectly fine, but any forward/backwards input is inverted. I modified the code to be able to invert each motor/can coder individually, which allowed me to get the behavior consistent on both modules, but any change just makes strafing and turning break. I have thought of inverting the joystick input on that axis for those two modules, which is not ideal but would probably work in the short term, but 364 uses part of the WPIlib swerve library for that, and short of copying a ton of code just to modify it slightly, I can’t find a better way to fix it.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2022-09-30T22:40:07.666Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":461,"reads":275,"readers_count":274,"score":2360.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":415657,"topic_slug":"mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted","display_username":"Dresden Friar","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/Team364/BaseFalconSwerve","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":22},{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/pid-controller-in-364s-base-swerve-drive-code/420463/9","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"PID Controller in 364's base swerve drive code","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":48750,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Team Captain & Programming - 1339 Angelbotics"},"post_url":"/t/mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted/415657/1","custom_user_title":"Team Captain & Programming - 1339 Angelbotics","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3085953,"name":"jhajel","username":"jhajel","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jhajel/{size}/95970_2.png","created_at":"2022-09-30T22:46:42.442Z","cooked":"<p>Is your IMU upside down?  We saw similar behavior when we went from mounting our NavX on the top of the belly pan to the bottom?  There is a procedure to reset the orientation of your IMU.  I didn’t handle this part, however.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2022-09-30T22:46:42.442Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":261,"readers_count":260,"score":82.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":415657,"topic_slug":"mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted","display_username":"jhajel","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":30898,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted/415657/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3085957,"name":"vargoose84","username":"vargoose84","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/vargoose84/{size}/165453_2.png","created_at":"2022-09-30T23:05:52.985Z","cooked":"<p>Could you let us know if you’re running field centric it’s robot centric code?</p>
<p>We’ve run into this problem several times, and I promise there is a combination of inverted motors and joystick inputs that will solve your problem.</p>
<p>For us it was the below (attempting to paste with my phone), it all depends on your coordinate system).</p>
<pre><code>       x = -Robot.xbox.getLeftY(); 
       y = -Robot.xbox.getLeftX(); 
       rot = -Robot.xbox.getRightX(); 

    public static TalonFXInvertType FRInvertType = TalonFXInvertType.Clockwise; 
     public static TalonFXInvertType FLInvertType = TalonFXInvertType.CounterClockwise; 
     public static TalonFXInvertType BRInvertType = TalonFXInvertType.Clockwise; 
     public static TalonFXInvertType BLInvertType = TalonFXInvertType.CounterClockwise;</code></pre>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2022-09-30T23:05:52.985Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":8,"reads":244,"readers_count":243,"score":93.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":415657,"topic_slug":"mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted","display_username":"vargoose84","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":30247,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3630 Assistant Coach - Stampede Robotics"},"post_url":"/t/mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted/415657/3","custom_user_title":"3630 Assistant Coach - Stampede Robotics","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3085959,"name":"Gavin Matthews","username":"bovlb","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bovlb/{size}/167232_2.png","created_at":"2022-09-30T23:24:02.718Z","cooked":"<p>Just a theory, but I suspect that the drive and turn (motors and encoders) both need to be inverted in those two modules.</p>
<p>At 0º and 180º, the turn inversion will disappear and you are left with drive inversion, so they go in the wrong direction.  At 90º and 270º, you get both inversions cancelling out, leaving them apparently working for strafe.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2022-09-30T23:30:48.340Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":9,"reads":213,"readers_count":212,"score":122.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":415657,"topic_slug":"mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted","display_username":"Gavin Matthews","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":38743,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)"},"post_url":"/t/mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted/415657/4","custom_user_title":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3086407,"name":"Dresden Friar","username":"Dresden","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/e9c0ed/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-10-03T17:35:07.049Z","cooked":"<p>Our IMU isn’t mounted upside-down, and to troubleshoot and eliminate the IMU as a problem, the robot has been propped up on blocks. There was also a point where most gyro code was removed just to make sure it didn’t have an impact, but this has since been reverted to no avail.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2022-10-03T17:35:07.049Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":146,"readers_count":145,"score":34.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":415657,"topic_slug":"mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted","display_username":"Dresden Friar","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":30898,"username":"jhajel","name":"jhajel","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jhajel/{size}/95970_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":48750,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Team Captain & Programming - 1339 Angelbotics"},"post_url":"/t/mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted/415657/6","custom_user_title":"Team Captain & Programming - 1339 Angelbotics","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3086408,"name":"Dresden Friar","username":"Dresden","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/e9c0ed/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-10-03T17:36:46.993Z","cooked":"<p>I’ve tried both field and robot centric, and they both work similarly as the robot is unable to change heading because we have it propped up on blocks. I am also a little apprehensive to invert the joysticks because it would break the two already working.</p>
<p>I have heard someone mention changing the coordinate system, so I am going to try to mess around with that.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2022-10-03T17:36:46.993Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":138,"readers_count":137,"score":57.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":415657,"topic_slug":"mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted","display_username":"Dresden Friar","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":30247,"username":"vargoose84","name":"vargoose84","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/vargoose84/{size}/165453_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":48750,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Team Captain & Programming - 1339 Angelbotics"},"post_url":"/t/mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted/415657/7","custom_user_title":"Team Captain & Programming - 1339 Angelbotics","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3086409,"name":"Dresden Friar","username":"Dresden","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/e9c0ed/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-10-03T17:38:46.555Z","cooked":"<p>I tried to do some combinations of inverting motors and offsetting by 180, but I was unable to get it to work. I will try to offset by 180 and invert everything to see if that works. I might have to make sure everything is actually getting inverted because I’m not confident the cancoders are actually changing. When I tried something similar before the motor turned the wrong way so it ended up perpendicular to where it needed to be while turning, even though both the encoder and motor were inverted together.</p>
<p>Also, I found out towards the end of my testing that ctre devices don’t love to get their settings changed repeatedly, so I have to do a full power cycle to make sure any changes I make actually take effect. I’ll probably retry everything.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2022-10-03T17:38:46.555Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":130,"readers_count":129,"score":41.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":415657,"topic_slug":"mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted","display_username":"Dresden Friar","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":38743,"username":"bovlb","name":"Gavin Matthews","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bovlb/{size}/167232_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":48750,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Team Captain & Programming - 1339 Angelbotics"},"post_url":"/t/mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted/415657/8","custom_user_title":"Team Captain & Programming - 1339 Angelbotics","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3086461,"name":"Dresden Friar","username":"Dresden","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/e9c0ed/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-10-03T22:49:34.224Z","cooked":"<p>I figured it out. The coordinate system was off, and so the modules were turning the wrong direction. After some inversions and fixing the coordinates, it all works great! Thanks everyone for the input!</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2022-10-03T22:49:34.224Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":82,"readers_count":81,"score":101.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":415657,"topic_slug":"mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted","display_username":"Dresden Friar","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":5}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":48750,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Team Captain & Programming - 1339 Angelbotics"},"post_url":"/t/mk4i-swerve-module-strafes-and-turns-fine-but-driving-forward-backward-is-inverted/415657/9","custom_user_title":"Team Captain & Programming - 1339 Angelbotics","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":5}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":5,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3237265,"name":"system","username":"system","avatar_template":"/uploads/default/original/4X/9/3/2/93234578e69f55873c63fc00fe2d0d85f23bce55.png","created_at":"2023-10-03T22:50:24.073Z","cooked":"<p>This topic was automatically closed 365 days after the last reply. New replies are no longer allowed.</p>","post_number":10,"post_type":3,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2023-10-03T22:50:24.073Z","reply_co